Lobstrosities are giant lobsters located in the south-east corner of the Underwater area of Fossil Island. Most weapons and shields cannot be equipped in this area. Weapons that can be equipped and used to kill lobstrosities include the merfolk trident, trident of the seas/swamp, brine sabre, and magic secateurs. Lobstrosities may also be killed with magic.

A fishbowl helmet cannot be worn in this area, but players can easily use the nearby air bubbles to replenish oxygen while fighting lobstrosities.

Seaweed spores will spawn around the area randomly. Though not confirmed, it appears that by re-entering the area by using the rift or underground tunnel after receiving three random seaweed spores spawns increases the amount of random seaweed spores that spawns afterwards.

12 July 2018
(update | poll)

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • Lobstrosity could be a reference to The Dark Tower series by Stephen King where creatures of the same name appear in the second book, The Drawing of the Three.
